HEADWORD: Bluegown
<hw>Blue"gown`</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One of a class of
paupers or pensioners, or licensed beggars, in Scotland, to whim
annually on the king's birthday were distributed certain alms, including
a blue gown; a beadsman.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Blue grass</ent>⟦br⟧
